```typescript
const wss = new WebSocket.Server({
    host: address,
    port: port,
    verifyClient: (info, verify) => {
        const id = getIdFromRequest(info.req);  // Get "id" param from URL parameters.
        if (id) {
            verify(true);
        } else {
            verify(false);
        }
    }
});
```

Suppose we have existing code like above, it works with current declaration.

But if we extend the declaration without optional, just like:

```typescript
callback: (res: boolean, code: number, message: string) => void) => void;
```

The tsc compiler will reject the code with error `[ts] Supplied parameters do not match any signature of call target.`

